The paper discusses the performance of the Approximate Message Passing (AMP) algorithm in high-dimensional statistical estimation problems such as compressed sensing and low-rank matrix estimation. This suggests that the paper could belong to several arXiv CS sub-categories related to these topics. 

cs.IT (Information Theory) is the most likely category as the paper deals with statistical estimation and signal processing, which are core topics in information theory. 

cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also a likely category as the paper discusses a scalable algorithm for high-dimensional regression, which is a common problem in machine learning. 

cs.SP (Signal Processing) is another likely category as the paper deals with compressed sensing and low-rank matrix estimation, which are important topics in signal processing. 

cs.MM (Multimedia) is a less likely category, but still possible as the paper deals with matrix estimation, which is relevant to multimedia applications such as image and video processing. 

cs.NA (Numerical Analysis) is also a less likely category, but possible as the paper discusses the performance of an algorithm and provides a concentration inequality, which are topics related to numerical analysis.
